Good place to get quick mexican food like a torta, quesadilla or some tacos. I have gotten the torta de milanesa de pollo like 10 times and it has been great every single time. The place is very simple but the location is extremely convenient, 1 block from the entrance to the C train on 161st street entrance. Some people complain that service is bad but it just may be a language barrier, as I always order in Spanish and have never had an issue. It’s not a place where you go to have a sit down meal, but rather call ahead and pick up to go. Definitely not the best Mexican food in the area, but convenient and tasty in its own right.

caption: The best tortas in NYC!  Another great hole in the wall mexican restaurant up in the ghetto.  I love the tortas here and the guacamole and chips.  The chips here are real chips - not cheap tostitos.  Cut tortillas that are fried crisp.  The guac has tomatos and lemon. So tasty.  I ordered the carne asada torte (grilled beef).  Full of lettuce, tomato, mayo and avocado.  It should also have refried beans in it.
